        "#CRM Customer Value Prediction using Machine Learning\n",
        "###Understanding the Business Problem\n",
        "We start with a CRM business problem:\n",
        "“Not all customers are equally valuable.\n",
        "Can we identify high-value customers using past purchase behavior?”\n",
        "This is important because businesses want to:\n",
        "Retain valuable customers\n",
        "Target them with personalized offers\n",
        "Optimize marketing costs"
      ]

      "source": [
        "### 10. Convert Date Columns"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 9,
      "id": "fb75d8a9",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "fb75d8a9"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "date_cols = [\n",
        "    'first_order_date',\n",
        "    'last_order_date',\n",
        "    'last_order_date_online',\n",
        "    'last_order_date_offline'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "for col in date_cols:\n",
        "    df[col] = pd.to_datetime(df[col])\n"
      ]
    },

      "cell_type": "markdown",

      "metadata": {
        "id": "ebfcfb14"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 11. Feature Engineering – Total Orders"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 10,
      "id": "101f108f",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "101f108f"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "df['total_orders'] = (\n",
        "    df['order_num_total_ever_online'] +\n",
        "    df['order_num_total_ever_offline']\n",
        ")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "8b1dec94",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8b1dec94"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 12. Feature Engineering – Total Customer Value"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 11,
      "id": "9ab9e21e",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9ab9e21e"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "df['total_value'] = (\n",
        "    df['customer_value_total_ever_online'] +\n",
        "    df['customer_value_total_ever_offline']\n",
        ")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "da5a0f71",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "da5a0f71"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 13. Recency Feature Engineering"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 12,
      "id": "a4350025",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "a4350025"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "reference_date = df['last_order_date'].max()\n",
        "\n",
        "df['recency_days'] = (reference_date - df['last_order_date']).dt.days\n",
        "df['tenure_days'] = (df['last_order_date'] - df['first_order_date']).dt.days\n"
      ]
    },

          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "(Index(['order_channel', 'last_order_channel', 'interested_in_categories_12'], dtype='object'),\n",
              " Index(['order_num_total_ever_online', 'order_num_total_ever_offline',\n",
              "        'customer_value_total_ever_offline', 'customer_value_total_ever_online',\n",
              "        'total_orders', 'total_value', 'recency_days', 'tenure_days'],\n",
              "       dtype='object'))"

          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 20
        }

      "source": [
        "\n",
        "cat_cols = X.select_dtypes(include='object').columns\n",
        "num_cols = X.select_dtypes(include=['int64','float64']).columns\n",
        "cat_cols, num_cols\n"
      ]

      "id": "210dfc3f",

      "source": [
        "\n",
        "preprocessor = ColumnTransformer([\n",

        "    ('cat', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore'), cat_cols)\n",
        "])\n"
      ]
    },
